Package tuitionmanager

Class Enrollment

java.lang.Object
tuitionmanager.Enrollment
public class Enrollment extends Object
This is a class that maintains a resizing array of EnrollStudent objects which represent an instance of a Enrollment object.

This class uses the EnrollStudent class to define an array of EnrollStudent objects which will be in the Enrollment instance.

Author:
Aryan Patel

  • Constructor Details

    • Enrollment

      Enrollment()
      This method creates a new Enrollment object containing an array of EnrollStudent objects and an int representing the count of EnrollStudent objects within the array. This is a no argument constructor.

  • Method Details

    • grow

      private void grow()
      This method takes care of resizing the array of EnrollStudent objects in Enrollment. The capacity is increased by 4 in the new enrollStudents array. Contents from the old array are copied over and the reference to the old array is discarded.

    • find

      private int find(EnrollStudent enrollStudent)
      This method finds a given EnrollStudent in the enrollStudents array, and returns the index of its position. If the EnrollStudent object is not in the array, then NOT_FOUND is returned.
      Parameters:
      enrollStudent - object input that is the student which needs to be found
      Returns:
      int which represents the index associated with the student position

    • getEnrollmentSize

      public int getEnrollmentSize()
      This method gets the value of the size variable representing the size of the enrollStudents array.
      Returns:
      int which contains the enrollStudent array size

    • getEnrollStudents

      public EnrollStudent[] getEnrollStudents()
      This method returns the enrollStudent array associated with an Enrollment object. This array contains objects of type EnrollStudent.
      Returns:
      array of type EnrollStudent containing EnrollStudent objects

    • contains

      public boolean contains(EnrollStudent enrollStudent)
      This method checks if a given EnrollStudent objects is contained within the enrollStudents array. This method utilizes the find() method and returns a boolean indicating whether find() was successful or not.
      Parameters:
      enrollStudent - object input that is to be checked whether it is present in the enrollStudent array or not
      Returns:
      boolean true or false representing whether the given EnrollStudent is in the array or not

    • add

      public void add(EnrollStudent enrollStudent)
      This method takes care of adding a given EnrollStudent to the enrollStudents array. It first checks if the student is already in the array before it adds the student. If the array is at capacity, the grow() method is called to increase the capacity.
      Parameters:
      enrollStudent - object input that is to be added into the enrollStudents array.

    • remove

      public void remove(EnrollStudent enrollStudent)
      This method takes care of removing a given EnrollStudent object from the enrollStudents array. First the index of removal is found and then the last EnrollStudent object in the array is used to replace the removed object.
      Parameters:
      enrollStudent - object input which is the EnrollStudent that needs to be found and removed

    • print

      public void print()
      This method takes care of printing the enrollStudents array. It first checks if the array is empty before proceeded to print each EnrollStudent line by line.
